10.commit_message: Bug 1507875 - Remove the customizable ui toolbarpaletteitem binding;r=Gijs  This removes the wrapping box inside the anonymous content, and replaces the anonymous label with an ::after CSS rule that sets text based on the [title] attribute.  Because it doesn't replicate the anonymous wrapping box with light DOM: - Calling JS don't need to be updated (the child added via appendChild   is still a direct descendant of the element). - Many CSS selectors don't need to be updated (if they were targeting the   slotted children as direct descendants. However, CSS selectors that were   targeting the anonymous content directly do need to be updated, since those   nodes are removed.  Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D12172
